</div>
</div>
<p><a name="Production" id="Production"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Tea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Production">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Production</span></h3>
<p>In 2003, world tea production was 3.15 million tonnes annually. The largest producer was <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a>, followed by <a href="/wiki/China" title="China">China</a> (the order has since reversed), followed by <a href="/wiki/Kenya" title="Kenya">Kenya</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sri_Lanka" title="Sri Lanka">Sri Lanka</a>. China is the only country today to produce in industrial quantities all different kinds of tea (white tea, yellow tea, green tea, blue-green tea, red tea and black tea).<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since May 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
